{"ts":"2026-06-23T20:35:34.182Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-nvgy"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"defineExtensionBlueprint: typed identity helper for partial blueprint fragments"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Add defineExtensionBlueprint(blueprint): TBlueprint to src/sdk/compose.ts — a zero-cost typed identity helper for a (partial) ExtensionBlueprint authored as its own module, the typed entry point of the modular declarative-authoring loop and natural companion to mergeExtensionBlueprints. Completes the define* symmetry: defineExtension (whole module), defineExtensionManifest (manifest), defineExtensionBlueprint (blueprint fragment). In TypeScript it preserves the narrow literal type while checking the fragment against the ExtensionBlueprint interface and gives contextual handler-parameter inference (the Vite defineConfig pattern), so each concern can be authored, exported, and unit-tested in its own .ts file then combined via mergeExtensionBlueprints. Re-exported from the SDK barrel; 100% line + docstring coverage; documented in docs/SDK.md Modular blueprints section."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Task"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"in_progress"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:extensions","area:sdk","authoring","dx"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-23T20:35:34.182Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-23T20:35:34.182Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/assignee","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-2p38"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-12tj","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-06-23T20:35:34.182Z"},{"id":"pm-2c28","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-06-23T20:35:34.1